the `monthly Z score' transformation, which takes the set of
values for a given month, calculates the mean and standard
deviation of that set of values, and then `standardizes' the
data by calculating the Z-score of each value, i.e., by sub-
tracting off the corresponding monthly mean and dividing
by the monthly standard deviation. The Z-score transfor-
mation also reduces temporal autocorrelation significantly.
Since we used time series spanning 41 years (12 monthly
measurements each year), we also detrended the data be-
fore our analysis.
For further details on these issues, we
refer the reader to [15] and [17].



